a) By examining permits in the book to see if they are filled in correctly and the right precautions have been identified;
b) By examining the actual execution of job and ensuring that it complies with what is addressed;
c) The frequency of the audit shall be random, but at least once a week;
d) Permit auditor submits a report to the sector chief/HOD of the plant. It is the responsibility of the plant HOD to take corrective actions as per the recommendations/suggestions given in the audit;
e) Permit audit findings shall be communicated to both issuer and acceptor for immediate compliance; and
f) Permits may be cancelled by the auditor at any moment if conditions are found not satisfactory/change of situation/change in agreed conditions.

